Spiced Simple Syrup: Place all of the ingredients in a medium saucepot, stir. Place on high heat, bring to a boil. Reduce heat, and simmer 5 minutes. Remove from heat, allow to cool completely. Pour syrup through a strainer to remove spices. Pour syrup into a jar with lid and store refrigerated. Shake before using. Sangria: Combine wine, 3/4 cup spiced simple syrup, sparkling water, orange juice, and fruit slices. Stir briskly. Serve over ice in large red wine glasses.